observations.recommendation:
We recommended that:

a. the Local Chief Executive direct the Municipal Agricultural Officer to submit monitoring report with supporting documents as to the status of the breeding stocks;

b. the Municipal Accountant to use the report submitted by the Municipal Agricultural Officer as a basis to properly classify the accounts.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor in coordination with the Sangguniang Bayan, adopt and implement cost measures to observe economy in the telephone and internet expenses taking into consideration the following:

Consider the use of postpaid plans offered by telecommunication networks with monthly billing;



Review the amounts of communication allowance in relation to the available landlines/mobile phones and internet connection and consider its reduction; 



Utilize alternative modes of communication such as internet for long-distance communication or consider communication network offering free call between and among networks; and 

Set reasonable limits on use of mobile phones to entitled officials. Any excess on the limit set shall be for the personal account of the users.



We also recommended that if cell cards/E-Load allowance shall be allowed, consider purchase in bulk by the GSO, following the required procurement procedures, and distribute the same in accordance with the guidelines and attached proof or evidence that expenses were incurred for official functions.

