We recommended that Management undertake the following:

a.	Stop the practice of allowing these job order/contracts of service/non-employees to attend trainings and seminars and claim the corresponding travelling allowances and per diems;

b.	Grant only the actual fare from the worker’s official station to the place of destination and vice versa whenever they are directed to perform tasks outside their official station;



c.	Allow only permanent or casual employee to act as official driver whenever there is a need to transport municipal employee/s to attend trainings, seminars and/or perform other tasks.

Further we recommended that succeeding claims of municipal workers hired under contract of service, job order contracts and non-employees on travelling allowances, per diems and incidental expenses in attending trainings/seminars and meetings and in performing various tasks outside official station will be disallowed in audit.

